This bug involves PCI probe workqueue flushing during CPU isolation changes — it requires triggering actual PCI device probing concurrent with housekeeping mask updates. kSTEP doesn't have PCI probe APIs and the bug's code path (`pci_call_probe` → `schedule_work_on`) can't be triggered from a kSTEP driver. Skipping.

